  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "## suggestion\r\nIf in `truffle dev` or `truffle console`.  Please ignore `truffle` if it is the first command.\r\n\r\n## use case 1: context switching\r\nMany times I'm in a loop of using `truffle test` or `truffle migrate --reset` while developing.\r\nI then drop into `truffle console`, to test things with the repl, but muscle memory gets me to type `TRUFFLE test` again.\r\n\r\n## use case 2: new users\r\nWhen I am teaching new users I usually show them `truffle test`, and get them to use it as part of their dev loop. When they complain that the tests take too long to run, I show them `truffle dev` and how it keeps truffle open, and they can then just use `test` to rapidly execute the tests.\r\nAgain due to muscle memory they type `truffle test` and question why it fails.",
